<p>What you&rsquo;re seeing is a custom Hugo theme, developed by following the first ~1/3 of the helpful book <a href="https://pragprog.com/titles/bhhugo/build-websites-with-hugo/"><em>Build Websites with Hugo</em></a> by Brian P. Hogan and then freestyling (aka typing semi-coherent questions into various search engines and LLMs until something started working).</p>
<h2 id="whats-up-with-the-name">What&rsquo;s up with the name?</h2>
<p>The word &ldquo;tlocrt&rdquo; (pronounced tlotsrt) means &ldquo;ground plan&rdquo; in Serbo-Croatian.
I picked it mainly because I liked how the word looked &mdash; it&rsquo;s kind of symmetric, but also not really.
Also it&rsquo;s not easy to find a cool domain name in 2024 that is also available&hellip;</p>
<p>The logo was inspired by the meaning of the word and contains artistic interpretations of elements of technical drawings.</p>
<h2 id="features">Features</h2>
<p>Features that took way more time than they should have include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Serving a downsized version of all images (unless the user clicks on an image &mdash; then they get all the pixels).</li>
<li>Responsive design (this means that things will be positioned and scaled differently, depending on your screen size).</li>
<li>Automatically generated &ldquo;Latest&rdquo; section on the homepage (the secret sauce was using <code>.Site.RegularPages</code> instead of <code>.Site.Pages</code>).</li>
<li><a href="https://tlocrt.com/feed.xml
">RSS feed</a></li>
</ul>
